 French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":67,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705188,"age":76,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705189,"age":111,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Robert DeTheydon was born about 1148, in Essex, England as the son of William de Theydon. He had at least 1 son. He died in his hometown."},"et":{"about 1148–":"umbes 1148–Surnud","1148–Male":"1148–Surnud","1168–1217":"1168–1217","1120–1194":"1120–1194","1217":"1217","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1148":"1148","1224":"1224","1168":"1168","about 1148":"umbes 1148","1120":"1120","1194":"1194","Essex, England":"Essex, England"},"fi":{"about 1148–":"noin 1148–Kuollut","1148–Male":"1148–Kuollut","1168–1217":"1168–1217","1120–1194":"1120–1194","1217":"1217","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1148":"1148","1224":"1224","1168":"1168","about 1148":"noin 1148","1120":"1120","1194":"1194","Essex, England":"Essex, England"},"fr":{"about 1148–":"environ 1148–Décédé","1148–Male":"1148–Décédé","1168–1217":"1168–1217","1120–1194":"1120–1194","1217":"1217","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1148":"1148","1224":"1224","1168":"1168","about 1148":"environ 1148","1120":"1120","1194":"1194","Essex, England":"Essex, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Robert DeTheydon est né environ 1148, à Essex, Angleterre, fils de William de Theydon. Il a eu au moins 1 fils. Il est décédé dans sa ville natale."},"de":{"about 1148–":"um 1148–Verstorben","1148–Male":"1148–Verstorben","1168–1217":"1168–1217","1120–1194":"1120–1194","1217":"1217","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1148":"1148","1224":"1224","1168":"1168","about 1148":"um 1148","1120":"1120","1194":"1194","Essex, England":"Essex, England","lifeSummary":"Robert DeTheydon wurde um 1148 in Essex, England, als Sohn von William de Theydon geboren. Er hatte mindestens 1 Sohn. Er starb in seinem Geburtsort."},"ht":{"about 1148–":"about 1148–Desede","1148–Male":"1148–Desede","1168–1217":"1168–1217","1120–1194":"1120–1194","1217":"1217","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1148":"1148","1224":"1224","1168":"1168","about 1148":"about 1148","1120":"1120","1194":"1194","Essex, England":"Essex, England"},"hu":{"about 1148–":"1